The paper studies a game-theoretic model of a supermarket with customers making strategic decisions to minimize their own expected total cost. This falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The model also involves queueing theory and stochastic processes, which could place it in the categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) or statistical inference (cs.SI). Finally, the paper uses a mean field model to analyze the behavior of the game as the number of queues approaches infinity, which could fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
